== Flask CRUD project for My.App.Person ==

User request: create a simple Flask project demonstrating CRUD on persistent class My.App.Person.

Steps taken:
1. Verified IRIS instance running on localhost:1972 (version 2026.2.0L)
2. Credentials confirmed: _system / xxxxxxx (changed for security)
3. Installed packages via uv: flask, intersystems-irispython (from /opt/isc/iris/dev/python/)
4. Attempted IRISObject API for class creation — failed (no setProperty method on IRISObject)
5. User redirected: use pandas to connect and manipulate data
6. Installed: pandas, sqlalchemy-iris
7. Rewrote setup_iris.py to use SQL DDL (CREATE TABLE My_App.Person)
8. Rewrote app.py to use pd.read_sql() for reads, SQLAlchemy text() for writes
   - df.to_sql() was tried for INSERT but failed: IRIS rejects dotted table names in CREATE TABLE
   - Fixed by using raw INSERT via text()
9. All CRUD endpoints verified working:
   - POST   /persons        → 201 Created
   - GET    /persons        → 200 list (pandas DataFrame → JSON)
   - GET    /persons/<id>   → 200 single record
   - PUT    /persons/<id>   → 200 partial update
   - DELETE /persons/<id>   → 204 No Content

